English

[edit]

Etymology 1

[edit]

Borrowed from Spanish Lupe.

Proper noun

[edit]

Lupe

  1. A female given name from Spanish.
  2. A male given name.

Etymology 2

[edit]

(This etymology is missing or incomplete. Please add to it, or discuss it at the Etymology scriptorium.)

Proper noun

[edit]

Lupe (plural Lupes)

  1. A surname.
Statistics
[edit]
  • According to the 2010 United States Census, Lupe is the 37391st most common surname in the United States, belonging to 596 individuals. Lupe is most common among American Indian/Alaska Native (47.99%), White (28.19%) and Hispanic/Latino (17.28%) individuals.

Further reading

[edit]
  • Hanks, Patrick, editor (2003), “Lupe”, in Dictionary of American Family Names, volume 2, New York: Oxford University Press, →ISBN, page 475.

Anagrams

[edit]
  • pule

German

[edit]

Etymology

[edit]

Ca. 1800, from French loupe.

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): /ˈluːpə/
  • Audio (Germany (Berlin)):(file)

Noun

[edit]

Lupe f (genitive Lupe, plural Lupen)

  1. magnifying glass
    Synonyms: Vergrößerungsglas, Brennglas

Declension

[edit]
Declension of Lupe [feminine]
singular plural
indef. def. noun def. noun
nominative eine die Lupe die Lupen
genitive einer der Lupe der Lupen
dative einer der Lupe den Lupen
accusative eine die Lupe die Lupen

Hyponyms

[edit]
  • Binokularlupe
  • Briefmarkenlupe
  • Fischlupe
  • Leselupe
  • Philatelistenlupe
  • Stereolupe

Derived terms

[edit]
  • lupenrein
  • unter die Lupe nehmen
  • Zeitlupe

Descendants

[edit]
  • Japanese: ルーペ (rūpe)
  • Korean: 루페 (rupe)

See also

[edit]
  • Linse

Latin

[edit]

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • (Classical Latin) IPA(key): [ˈɫʊ.pɛ]
  • (modern Italianate Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): [ˈluː.pe]

Proper noun

[edit]

Lupe

  1. vocative singular of Lupus

Spanish

[edit]

Pronunciation

[edit]
  • IPA(key): /ˈlupe/ [ˈlu.pe]
  • Rhymes: -upe
  • Syllabification: Lu‧pe

Proper noun

[edit]

Lupe f

  1. a diminutive of the unisex given name Guadalupe
